investigation.title: Effects of low-dose oxygen ions and protons on cardiac function and structure in male C57BL/6J mice (echocardiogram/ultrasonography)
investigation.description: Purpose: Astronauts traveling beyond low Earth orbit will be exposed to high linear energy transfer charged particles. Because there is concern about the adverse effects of space radiation on the cardiovascular system, this study assessed cardiac function and structure and immune cell infiltration in a mouse model of charged particle irradiation.
